  "rationale": "This claim is appropriate for payment. Both ECGs are medically necessary for a patient with atrial fibrillation (I48.91). While CPT 93000 has an MUE limit of 1 per day, the provider correctly used modifier 76 on the second line to indicate a repeat procedure by the same physician. The clinical note clearly documents that a baseline ECG was performed, followed by a repeat ECG after an acute symptomatic episode the same day, with both interpreted by the same attending cardiologist. This is a legitimate clinical scenario where a repeat ECG is warranted. No NCCI bundling issues, no duplicates, modifiers are valid, and documentation supports both procedures.",
